{"title":"•Ampicilina","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/•Ampicilina-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"• Ampicilina","guid":"jdOR71_d-2Xu6wlg5yBU4Q","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Uso y\\NDosificación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Descripción: Ampicilina (y Amoxicilina) son aminopenicilinas con actividad predecible contra\\Nestreptococos, la mayoría de enterococos, Listeria, clostridios y una variedad de otras bacterias\\Nanaerobias.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en Adultos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"4","parent":"3","text":"• Dosis usual:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"3","text":"• Oral: 250-500\\Nmg po q6h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"3","text":"• IV: 1-2 gm IV q4-6h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en Pediatría","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"• Dosis (Edad >28 días):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"• Oral: 50-100 mg/kg/día\\N(dividido q6h), máx 2 gm","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"7","text":"• IV (estándar): 200 mg/kg/día\\N(dividido q6h), máx 8 gm","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"7","text":"• IV (meningitis): 300-400 mg/kg/día\\N(dividido q4h), máx 12 gm","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste Renal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"• Peso corporal y depuración\\Nde creatinina (CrCl):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"• Función renal normal:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"12","text":"• Vida media: 1.2 hr","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"• ESRD:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"12","text":"• Vida media: 7-20 hr","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"12","text":"• Dosis (función renal\\Nnormal): 1-2 gm IV q4-6h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"12","text":"• CrCl >50-90:\\N1-2 gm q4-6h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"12","text":"• CrCl 30-50:\\N1-2 gm q6-8h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"12","text":"• CrCl 10-30: 1-2\\Ngm q8-12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"12","text":"• HD: 1-2 gm q12h (una dosis\\Nen día de diálisis AD)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"12","text":"• CAPD: 500 mg\\N- 1 gm q12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"12","text":"• CRRT: 1-2 gm q8-12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"12","text":"• SLED: Sin datos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"26","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste Hepático: Ninguno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"1","text":"Otros Ajustes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"• ECMO: Las concentraciones séricas pueden\\Nno verse significativamente alteradas por\\NECMO. Ver tabla para detalles.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"1","text":"Efectos Adversos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• Alergia: Rash común con todos\\Nlos antibióticos β-lactámicos,\\Nincluyendo Ampicilina.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"• Mononucleosis infecciosa (EBV): 65-100%\\Ndesarrollan rash; 90% de los pacientes con LLC y\\N15-20% de los pacientes que toman alopurinol. No\\Netiquetar como alérgico a penicilina.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"• Alergia verdadera a Ampicilina: ↑ Riesgo de\\Nreacciones cruzadas con cefalosporinas orales con\\Ncadenas laterales R1 idénticas: Cefaclor,\\NCephalexin, Cephradine, Loracarbef.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"29","text":"• Efectos adversos: Fiebre, rash (5%), anafilaxia (raro),\\N+Coombs, neutropenia, eosinofilia (22%), trombocitopenia\\N(raro), ↑ PT/PTT, náuseas/vómitos (2%), diarrea (10%),\\Ncolitis por C. difficile (raro).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"1","text":"Riesgo en Embarazo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"• Categoría de riesgo FDA 1:\\NSin evidencia de toxicidad en\\Nhumanos o animales.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"• Uso durante lactancia: Concentraciones bajas en\\Nleche, no se esperan efectos adversos. Monitorear\\Ntoxicidad GI en el infante.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"0","text":"Espectro\\NAntimicrobiano","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"RECOMENDADO ++ (7)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"• Actinomyces sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"• B. burgdoferi","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"38","text":"• E. faecalis (VS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"38","text":"• L. monocytogenes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"38","text":"• N. meningitidis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"38","text":"• P. multocida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"38","text":"• Peptostreptococci","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"37","text":"ACTIVO + (13)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"• Arcanobacter sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"• C. diphtheriae","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"46","text":"• C. trachomatis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"• Clostridium sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"46","text":"• Kingella sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"46","text":"• Leptospira sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"46","text":"• P. acnes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"46","text":"• P. mirabilis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"46","text":"• Strep. agalactiae gp (B)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"46","text":"• Strep. anginosus gp","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"46","text":"• Strep. gp C, F, G","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"46","text":"• Strep. pneumo